|!Path |!Purpose |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/draft/<type-key>` |Creator's draft for in-progress instance |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/instances-overview/search` |''Instances Overview'': node search-box text |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/graph-modal` |Graph tooltip modal mode switch ŌĆö `edit` field (live editor for that instance), `delete` field (confirm dialog), or `kind-tid` + `host` fields (create-child form). Deleted on Close/Cancel/Create/Delete |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/graph-modal/draft` |Draft for the graph tooltip's ''Add child'' create form (parent pre-set, defaults applied; re-seeded on every tooltip button click) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/__graph-created` |Transient capture of the just-created tiddler title from the graph-modal create flow |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/context/direction` |''Context'' preview: parent-tree direction ŌĆö `to` (descendants, default) or `from` (ancestors) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/context/depth` |''Context'' preview: number of `parent`-tree levels to show (1ŌĆō5, default 2) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/context/edge-fields` |''Context'' preview: ref-field keys drawn as edges, stored in the `edges` field (titlelist; defaults to `parent`, and floors back to `parent` if every field is deselected) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/context/hidden-types` |''Context'' preview: type keys hidden from the graph (titlelist; empty/absent = all types shown) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/edit-mode/<target-tid>` |Per-instance toggle between popup and inline edit mode in stream-view |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/ta/<target-tid>/<field-key>` |Typeahead search-input state for a ref field |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/creator/selected-type` |Currently-selected type in the creator |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/type-builder/selected` |Currently-edited type in the type-builder |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/type-builder/preview-draft` |Live editor preview's target |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/cascade-draft/<type-key>` |Manage-kinds ''+ Create new instance'' draft (per type) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/cascade-preview-draft/<type-key>` |Manage-kinds side-preview form draft (per type ŌĆö survives drill-in/out) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/cascade-spawn-draft/<parent-tid>/<parent-field>/<ref-type-key>` |Draft for a nested ''+ Create new <X>'' spawn from a ref-field picker (per spawn point ŌĆö survives drill-in/out and supports arbitrary nesting depth) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/create-here-draft/<host-tid>/<target-field>/<ref-type-key>` |Draft for the ''Create hereŌĆ”'' per-instance action (parallel to the spawn draft, but the back-ref direction is inverted ŌĆö host title is pre-set on the NEW instance's `<target-field>` rather than written to the host's field). |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/__spawn-result` |Transient capture of the just-spawned tiddler title (used by `kind.cascade-spawn-save` to wire into the parent's ref field) |
|`<create-here-draft-tid>/wizidx` |Current 1-based step index for a creation-wizard run (per draft; set to `1` on drill-open, bumped by ŌåÉ Back / Next ŌåÆ, deleted on Ō£ō Create) |

!! Creation wizards (multi-step guided create)

A wizard turns the cascade-palette ''Create hereŌĆ”'' flow for a kind from one all-fields form into an ordered sequence of steps, each asking only the field(s) the designer assigns ŌĆö so an inexperienced user is guided to a valid instance without ever opening //Edit fields//. Define one step per tiddler:

|!Field |!Required |!Meaning |
|tag |Yes |`$:/tags/rimir/kind/wizard-step` |
|`ca-wizard-kind` |Yes |Target type-key being created (e.g. `topic`). |
|`ca-wizard-context` |No |Host type-key this wizard variant applies to (e.g. `person` ŌĆö the kind you launched ''Create hereŌĆ”'' from). Empty = the ''default'' wizard for the kind. Resolution per (target, host): the context-specific step set wins; if none exists, the default set is used. |
|`ca-order` |Yes |Step order within the wizard (numeric, `nsort`ed). |
|`ca-step-name` |Yes |Short prompt shown in the progress row (//Step n of m ┬Ę <name>//). Avoid `"` in the value. |
|`ca-step-fields` |Yes |Space-separated field keys to ask for in this step. Each renders via the standard field editor (`kind.field-edit-json`) ŌĆö text, enum, ref picker, date, etc. |
|`ca-step-hint` |No |Longer help text for the step. |
|`ca-step-pick-tree` |No |`yes`\|`tree`\|`flat` turns a ''single-`ca-step-fields`'' ref step into the ''switchable'' picker (see below): a drillable namespace ''tree'' and a ''flat'' candidate list the user can flip between at runtime. The value is the //initial// layout (`yes`/`tree` ŌåÆ tree, `flat` ŌåÆ flat); absent = the plain flat field editor (no switch). Use on the //final// step (pick = create). |
|`ca-step-pick-roots` |No |Filter for the tree layout's root nodes. Default `$:/config/rimir/kind/wizard/pick-roots` = `[all[tiddlers]!is[system]cp-child-of[]]`. Children come from `$:/config/rimir/kind/wizard/pick-children` (= `cp-child-of<currentTiddler>`, the namespace tree). |

''Behaviour:'' the whole wizard is one drill stage backed by `<draft>/wizidx`. ''Next ŌåÆ'' is blocked (Ōøö row) until the current step's fields pass `kind.viol-any`; the final ''Ō£ō Create'' re-checks the whole draft via `kind.any-invalid` then runs `kind.finalize-create` (title-formula, validation, auto-children all behave as in the Creator). The launch context pre-seeds the back-ref (parent or ref field), but a `parent`/ref step lets the user redirect it. ''Esc'' cancels the whole wizard. ŌÜĀ’ĖÅ Every ''required'' field of the kind must appear in some step (or carry a `default`), otherwise the final ''Create'' stays Ōøö-blocked.

''Hands-free landing.'' A single-field step ''auto-opens'' its one input ŌĆö a text/enum step lands directly in value-edit mode (Enter commits ŌåÆ Next), a ref/tree step lands directly in the picker (uses cascade-palette's `ca-auto` / `ca-auto-token`). A non-selectable heading bar above the input names each step (cascade-palette `ca-stage-heading` / `ca-next-heading`). So a guided create is mostly just ''type ┬Ę Enter ┬Ę pick ┬Ę Enter''.

''Switchable picker'' (`ca-step-pick-tree: yes|tree|flat`). The step opens a parent/ref picker with ''two layouts'' the user flips between at runtime via a pinned ''Ōćä Switch'' row at the top:
* ''Tree'' ŌĆö a drillable hierarchy (same structure as the //By Namespace// view): ''Right-arrow'' descends into a node's children. Universe = the `cp-child-of` namespace tree (any tiddler), overridable via `ca-step-pick-roots` + the `pick-roots` / `pick-children` config tiddlers.
* ''Flat'' ŌĆö the field's valid ref candidates (`kind.ref-candidates`, i.e. instances of the field's ref-types) as a single non-drillable list.

In ''both'' layouts ''Enter'' on a row commits it as the field value AND finalises the instance ŌĆö choosing IS the create (`ca-enter-fires`) ŌĆö each focused row shows its kind ''context graph'' in the side preview, and after the create the palette returns to the entity you launched ''Create hereŌĆ”'' from (`ca-after-fire: pop-to-actions`) rather than closing. The chosen layout is ''remembered per step'' in a persisted JSON-map config tiddler (`$:/config/rimir/kind/wizard/pick-mode`, keyed by step title), so a user's preference sticks across creates. The Ōćä row lives at the picker root; deep in the tree, back out (Esc) to reach it.

!! Engine functions (engine.tid)

|!Function |!Returns |
|`kind.types-all()` |All type tiddlers |
|`kind.locate-type(type-key)` |The type tiddler with that key |
|`kind.active-ns()` |Current active namespace string |
|`kind.belongs-to-ns(active-ns)` |Filter predicate; non-empty if `<currentTiddler>` is in scope |
|`kind.namespaces-all()` |Unique sorted list of all namespaces used by any type |
|`kind.field-keys(type-tid)` |Ordered list of field keys |
|`kind.field-typed(type-tid, field-key)` |`typed` value of the field |
|`kind.field-caption(type-tid, field-key)` |Field caption (falls back to key) |
|`kind.constraints(type-tid, field-key)` |All constraint strings |
|`kind.has-constraint(type-tid, field-key, name)` |Non-empty if constraint present |
|`kind.constraint-num(type-tid, field-key, prefix)` |Numeric value of `min:N` / `max:N` |
|`kind.options(type-tid, field-key)` |Enum option strings |
|`kind.ref-types(type-tid, field-key)` |Allowed ref target type keys |
|`kind.ref-candidates(type-tid, field-key)` |All currently-existing target instances. When `ref-types` is empty, falls back to all kind-instances in the wiki (any `kind.type`). |
|`kind.eval-title(type-tid, target-tid)` |Computed title for an instance |
|`kind.is-child-kind(type-tid)` `kind.parent-kinds-of(type-tid)` `kind.parent-kinds-include(type-tid, candidate)` |Child-kind predicates/getters. Non-empty if `kind.parent-kinds` is set. |
|`kind.top-level-types()` `kind.child-kinds-of(parent-key)` |Filtered views of `kind.types-all()` ŌĆö top-level (no parent-kinds) vs children of a given parent type-key. |
|`kind.has-ref-field-to(type-tid, target-key)` `kind.ref-back-fields-of(type-tid, target-key)` `kind.kinds-with-back-ref-to(target-key)` |"Create hereŌĆ”" discovery ŌĆö find kinds whose ref-typed fields list the target as a valid `ref-types` member, and the field-keys on those kinds. |
|`kind.create-here-target-kinds(host-key)` `kind.has-create-here-options(host-tid)` |Union of child kinds + ref-back kinds; the cascade-palette ''Create hereŌĆ”'' action's `ca-applies` gates on this. |
|`kind.referencing-instances(host-tid, source-tid, field-key)` |Reverse-reference core: instances of `source-tid`'s kind whose `field-key` references `host-tid`. The building block for the ''Referenced byŌĆ”'' drill and any two-hop reverse lookup. |
|`kind.qual-source-kinds(host-tid)` `kind.qual-back-fields(host-tid, source-tid)` `kind.back-rel-count(host-tid)` |Reverse-nav discovery ŌĆö which source kinds reference the host (through a `back-nav`-enabled field with Ōēź1 instance), the qualifying field-keys per source kind, and the total relation count (1 ŌåÆ skip straight to the instance list; Ōēź2 ŌåÆ entry-level relation rows). |
|`kind.back-sort-field-eff(source-tid)` `kind.inst-group-val(source-tid, inst-tid)` |Reverse-nav listing helpers ŌĆö effective sort field (`kind.back-sort-by`, default `modified`) and an instance's group value (`kind.back-group-by`). |
|`kind.auto-children-array(type-tid)` `kind.auto-children-indexes(type-tid)` `kind.has-auto-children(type-tid)` |Raw access to the parent kind's `kind.auto-children` JSON array. |
|`kind.auto-child-kind-at(type-tid, idx)` `kind.auto-child-fields-at(type-tid, idx)` `kind.auto-child-field-value-at(type-tid, idx, field-key)` |Walk one entry ŌĆö get the child kind's type-key, the field-key list, and individual field values that should override the child kind's defaults. |
|`kind.viol-required(...)` `kind.viol-min(...)` `kind.viol-max(...)` `kind.viol-unique(...)` `kind.viol-unique-wiki(...)` `kind.viol-title(...)` `kind.viol-format-url(...)` `kind.viol-format-email(...)` `kind.viol-format-phone(...)` `kind.viol-parent-kind(...)` |Validation predicates (non-empty = violation). `kind.viol-parent-kind` checks that a child kind's instance has a `parent` whose `kind.type` is in the kind's `parent-kinds` list. |
|`kind.any-invalid(type-tid, type-key, target-tid)` |Non-empty if any constraint is violated on any field |
|`kind.shorten`, `kind.display`, `kind.resolve-ref` |Display helpers |

!! Engine procedures (engine.tid)

|!Procedure |!Effect |
|`kind.compute-default(type-tid, field-key, target-tid)` |Evaluates the field's `default` filter against `<target-tid>`-as-source via `subfilter`. Returns the first result (or empty). Used by `apply-defaults-to` / `force-apply-defaults` and available to any other code that wants to preview the computed default. |
|`kind.apply-defaults-to(type-tid, target-tid)` |Stamps `kind.type` + walks all defaultable fields and writes `compute-default` onto `target-tid` for fields currently blank (idempotent ŌĆö leaves user-set fields alone). Used by every create path before save, AND re-fired from field-input action chains after each ref/enum change so dependent defaults populate. |
|`kind.force-apply-defaults(type-tid, target-tid)` |Like `apply-defaults-to` but unconditional. Used by the //Reset to defaults// flow. |
|`kind.apply-auto-children(parent-tid, type-tid)` |Walks `type-tid.kind.auto-children` and materialises each entry as a new tiddler with `parent: <<parent-tid>>` + per-entry `fields` overrides + the child kind's own field defaults. Transcluded by `kind.finalize-create` //nested inside// its `$action-createtiddler`, with `parent-tid` taken from `<<createTiddler-title>>` (the real post-uniquification title ŌĆö a sibling read of `$savetitle` is evaluated at render time and sees a stale value, so the nesting is load-bearing). Entries pointing at non-existent kinds are skipped silently. Not recursive. |

